PACIFIC COAST SHIPBUILDING COMPANY, a Corporation, Petitioner, v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE, Respondent. No. 7707. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Dec. 17, 1934. Frank J. Wideman, Asst. Ally. Gen., and Robert H. Jackson, Asst. Gen. Counsel, Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. G., for respondent.

Before WILBUR, SAWTELLE, and GARRECHT, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of respondent, ordered petition to review in this cause dismissed for failure of petitioner to lile record and docket cause; mandate forthwith.
